Atmo Desktop Framework (Qt6/KF6)

Dependencies (Ubuntu/Kubuntu 26.04-era)
- build-essential
- cmake
- ninja-build
- extra-cmake-modules
- qt6-base-dev
- libkf6windowsystem-dev

Recommended for full feature build
- qt6-tools-dev qt6-tools-dev-tools
- libkf6coreaddons-dev libkf6config-dev libkf6configwidgets-dev
- libkf6kcmutils-dev libkf6i18n-dev libkf6guiaddons-dev
- libkdecorations3-dev (optional decoration plugin)
- dbusmenu-qt6 CMake package if your distro ships it (optional DBus menu integration)
- libxcb1-dev libx11-dev (optional X11 fallback)

Configure
cmake -S . -B build -GNinja \
  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo \
  -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr \
  -DATMO_BUILD_DECORATION=ON \
  -DATMO_BUILD_KCM=ON \
  -DATMO_ENABLE_X11_FALLBACK=ON \
  -DBUILD_MANAGER=ON

Build
cmake --build build -j"$(nproc)"

Install
sudo cmake --install build

Installed module paths (Plasma 6)
- Style plugin: `${KDE_INSTALL_QTPLUGINDIR}/styles`
- Decoration plugin: `${KDE_INSTALL_PLUGINDIR}/org.kde.kdecoration3`
- KCM plugin: `${KDE_INSTALL_PLUGINDIR}/plasma/kcms/systemsettings`
- KDecoration3 KCM hook: `${KDE_INSTALL_PLUGINDIR}/org.kde.kdecoration3.kcm`
- Default config template: `${KDE_INSTALL_DATADIR}/atmo/NSE.conf`

Uninstall
sudo cmake --build build --target uninstall
